# ── Catch-all: any *.html inside a section → section listing
# CF Pages permissive default serves the closest matching index.html for unknown paths
# (e.g., /articles/any-slug.html returns articles/index.html content). This creates fake
# URLs that all serve the same listing page, triggering "Alternate page with proper
# canonical tag" failures in GSC. These rules force 301 to the canonical section URL.
/articles/*.html /articles/ 301
/education/*.html /education/ 301
/investing/*.html /investing/ 301
/market-analysis/*.html /market-analysis/ 301

# Defensive: any other section/slug.html → /section/

# ── Catch-all: any *.html inside a section → section listing (for sections without)
# CF Pages serves the homepage HTML for ANY unknown path with 200 (no 404.html defined).
# This is causing Google to index hundreds of phantom URLs all serving homepage content
# with canonical /, triggering "Page with redirect" and "Alternate page" failures.
/about/*.html /about/ 301
/contact/*.html /contact/ 301
/disclaimer/*.html /disclaimer/ 301
/privacy/*.html /privacy/ 301
/terms/*.html /terms/ 301

# ── Catch-all catch-all: anything else with .html that doesn't resolve → /
